e from a non-planes capable guild.  Now these rules are somewhat flexible, however, it has always been KCoG policy to follow the KGC rules as much as possible.<br><br>Of course, KCoG generally gets so many people that no single person is necessary to the success of the raid.  It is one reason I always took everyone who showed up.  That relieved me of the possibility of having to defend myself on the KGC boards for violating the rules.<br><br>The long and short of it is, yes you are welcome so long as you are not vital to the success of the raid and are aware that should any cuts need to be made due to numbers, KCoG policy is to cut from the planes capable guilds first, even if you are a higher level than someone from a non-planes capable guild.<br><br>Kellory Silverstar<br>The Watchmen<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubenus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Benus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/4/02 12:07:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=309.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: KCoG question about raids..</span><hr size=1> Thank you very much for your quick answer..<br><br>I really appreciate it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p><img src="http://vanissa.homestead.com/files/benussig.jpg"><br><font face="verdana" size="1">Enchanter lvl 50, Master: Jeweler (195) Researcher (140) <ahref="http://www.geocities.com/wildelf1/hcmain.htm